# 12. Conclusion

A parameterized Low-Power ALU was successfully designed and verified using Verilog HDL. The project demonstrates important digital design concepts including arithmetic logic implementation, flag generation, operand isolation, clock-enable design, low-power techniques, and functional verification. All test cases passed successfully, validating the correctness of the design.

